      • extendedVersion

        GremlinKryo.Builder extendedVersion(byte extendedVersion)
        If using custom classes it might be useful to tag the version stamped to the serialization with a custom value, such that Kryo serialization at 1.0.0 would have a fourth byte for an extended version. The user supplied fourth byte can then be used to ensure the right deserializer is used to read the data. If this value is not supplied then it is written as Byte.MIN_VALUE. The value supplied here should be greater than or equal to zero.

      • compliant

        GremlinKryo.Builder compliant(BiPredicate<Byte,Byte> compliant)
        By default the extendedVersion(byte) is checked against what is read from an input source and if those values are equal the version being read is considered "compliant". To alter this behavior, supply a custom compliance Predicate to evaluate the value read from the input source (i.e. first argument) and the value marked in the GremlinKryo instance {i.e. second argument}. Supplying this function is useful when versions require backward compatibility or other more complex checks. This function is only used if the extendedVersion(byte) is set to something other than its default.
